Rosebay is also located on-site, offering craft cocktails and light fare. Virtual golf with over 50 golf courses, a fitness center are available. A business center, meeting facilities, and 24-hour room services can also be found onsite.

The Seattle Center is a 5 minutes drive away, Pike Place Market is a 7 minutes' walk, and Pioneer Square is a 6 minutes' walk from the hotel.

name: Seattle Coffee Tour
description: Do you love coffee, espresso, and more? We have our Road Dog's Seattle Coffee Tours leaving daily to visit some of the best cafe's and coffee roasters in the beautiful Pacific Northwest. Road Dog Tours is always looking to bring our guests the best experiences and new ways to explore Seattle. You will taste many different types of coffee drinks, learn about the different types of coffee beans and the roasting process.

review.name: not worth taking a tour for this
review.reviewBody: We had higher expectations of this tour. Dave was a nice guy, guy's a character, he's really cool, but the tour lacks a more context insight into the process of how coffee is made and the history of coffee culture in Seattle. To put it in a nutshell, you just drive around to three different coffeehouses in the city (which were great, don't get me wrong). It is just something that you can do on your own in the city.

name: Seattle Distillery Tours
description:
On a distillery tour with Road Dogs, you'll be able to see (and taste!) for yourself the intense dedication that goes into producing the finest local spirits. Our2.5 hour tour will introduce you to three of the area's 20+ distilleries, including the history and daily operations of each. Not only will you have a fabulous time learning how favorites like vodka, gin, whiskey and other spirits are made.

There's no better way to see Seattle, socialize, and sip sensational spirits, all in an afternoon! We make it easy by transporting guests to all of the fun and informative stops on the tour.

review.name: Excellent time
review.reviewBody: Our tour was excellent and we had a lot of fun.  Our tour guide Dave was very friendly and knowledgeable.  I would recommend this tour to anyone who likes beer and a good time.

itemListElement.name: Whale Watching & Wildlife Tour, Seattle Pier 69

name: Whale Watching & Wildlife Tour, Seattle Pier 69
description: Set out on a whale watching cruise from Seattle to see gray whales! This cruise will take you through the Puget Sound in search of the whales that migrate along Washingtons coast every year. The catamarans viewing decks offer excellent vantage points to spot the whales and an expert naturalist provides informative commentary. With hundreds of whales passing through these waters during the seasonal migration, there are sure to be plenty of sightings and great photo opportunities!

review.name: ACCESSIBILITY - 1 Star - Staff - 5 Stars
review.reviewBody:
This could have been great, but the boat is not really suitable for wheel chair users. If we were just getting from Point A to Point B, everything would be fine BUT.. This is a WHALE WATCHING tour, and viewing is not really easily achieved. 

The staff, on the other hand, was EXCEPTIONAL. They did everything possible to accommodate  the person in the wheelchair, but that was extremely limited. The naturalist tour guide was great as well. We just couldnt see what she was describing.

We enjoyed ourselves, but that could have been easily achieved with just a boat ride.

review.name: Incredible - a must for nature lovers!
review.reviewBody:
Absolutely incredible experience, would highly recommend to anyone spending time in Seattle!

The boat goes from right in the centre to Puget Sound, giving you spectacular views of the Seattle skyline and its surrounding nature. 

We got to see an incredible array of wildlife, including bald eagles, stella sealions, grey whales and orca! The captain stayed at each for the right amount of time to enjoy each wildlife encounter, while also allowing to see as much as possible in the time.

Not only that, but throughout the onboard marine experts were giving valuable and interesting commentary on the nature, and also brought round things to touch and interact with to make the whole experience more educational.

If you can afford it, the premium seating at the edge of the boat gives great views when you want to sit inside so would recommend, but if its a nice day you can go on the top deck/front deck which makes the viewing experience so special. It does get cold though as the boat drives quite fast so bring jumpers/coats!

There is also food/drinks on board,  but I would recommend bringing a sandwich or something, as there wasn't too much available and you don't want to miss anything while you're queuing!

It is on the pricey end, but thoroughly worth the cost.

review.name: Great Experience, two for One
review.reviewBody: We saw both gray whales and orcas. A rare occurrence according to our naturalist guide. The weather was cold (52 degrees) and light rain during parts of the tour, so bring layers and a rain cover layer.

review.name: Gray Whale Watch
review.reviewBody:
The ship is very comfortable and the crew hospitable. We enjoyed the naturalist educating us about the whales we saw. 

It is hard to hear the announcements in the back of the ship over the roar of the engines. 

The gray whales are difficult to see because they rarely come out of the water. You can see their exhale, their backs, and the occasional tail fin. And they are far away - of course, that is their natural behavior, so we understand that no one can do anything about that! The orca tours later in the year are better.

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: Very informative and our nature guide gave lots of useful and unique information that made the tour an overall enriching experience. Lots of time to experience the whales.

review.name: Overpriced for 1 whale
review.reviewBody: Overpriced for what you get. We saw one whale and barely saw it. They make it sound like you will see a pod of whales, nope, its just one and it comes up once every 5 min to get a breath of air so you hardly see it at all. Go to Sea World. Its cheaper and you see more.

review.name: Saw whales
review.reviewBody:
We had a great time, make sure you dress appropriately as it was ffffreeezing!

We saw whales and sea lions and the boat was nice enough, with food and drink on board.

Only advice to the company, if you are going to operate a clock based location, perhaps stop getting the boat to move once announced, you move around to see it and end up in wrong location 2 seconds later

review.name: looking for whales.
review.reviewBody:
booked a trip with clipper vacations.
Found the parking center for the car where you get a discount.
This is a long trip so plan ahead as you get back in the afternoon.
The boat trip was very pleasant with room inside and out.
We were there in April not the best season for whales but managed to see three of them as well as other sea life.
The staff on board were good and knowledge.
The weather was good to us no rain.
